    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-08-21T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-08-21T14:00:00-05:00" n="136"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d136">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/1963</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-08-21T15:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 21, 1918, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your August 17, 5 p.m. Should attempt be made to put the proposed regulations
                    into force you will make protest as suggested upon the basis of the Department’s
                    telegraphic instruction of October 13, 2 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d136fn1">
                        <ref target="frus1917#pg_149">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1917, p. 149</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
